  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Working for Irish Clients on Stamp 0</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Stamp 0 explicitly prohibits working for Irish employers or clients. This isn't a technicality—it's a core condition. Violating this can result in deportation and future immigration problems.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Assuming Stamp 0 Counts Toward Citizenship</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Stamp 0 time is NOT reckonable residence. It does NOT count toward Irish citizenship or permanent residence. If long-term settlement is your goal, STEP or employment-based permits are necessary.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Letting Health Insurance Lapse</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Private health insurance is a visa condition for Stamp 0. If your insurance lapses, you're technically in violation. Ensure continuous coverage and renew before expiration.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Dublin Housing</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The Dublin rental crisis is real. Don't arrive expecting to quickly find an apartment. Budget for temporary accommodation (Airbnb, hotels) for potentially 4-8 weeks while searching. Consider Cork or Galway if Dublin costs are prohibitive.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Getting Explicit Remote Work Permission</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">When applying for Stamp 0, specifically request permission to do remote work for foreign clients. Your permission letter should explicitly state this. Generic Stamp 0 without this clarification creates ambiguity.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Healthcare in Ireland -->
  <section id="healthcare" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare in Ireland</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Ireland has a two-tier healthcare system: public (HSE) and private. Stamp 0 holders have NO access to public healthcare and MUST rely entirely on private insurance.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Healthcare Access by Status</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-red-200 bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3">Stamp 0 Holders</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-800">
          <li>✗ NO access to public HSE services</li>
          <li>✗ NO medical cards</li>
          <li>✗ Must pay privately for everything</li>
          <li>• Private insurance MANDATORY</li>
          <li>• Emergency care available (billed)</li>
          <li>• Prescriptions at full cost</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">With Private Insurance</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>✓ Private hospitals (Beacon, Blackrock)</li>
          <li>✓ Faster consultations</li>
          <li>✓ Choice of specialist</li>
          <li>✓ Shorter wait times</li>
          <li>✓ Private rooms</li>
          <li>✓ Direct billing often available</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Healthcare Costs Without Insurance</h3>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>GP visit:</strong> €55-70</li>
      <li><strong>Specialist consultation:</strong> €150-300</li>
      <li><strong>Emergency room:</strong> €100+ (if not admitted)</li>
      <li><strong>Hospital bed:</strong> €80/day (public) or €800+/day (private)</li>
      <li><strong>MRI scan:</strong> €200-400</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Irish private hospitals:</strong> Dublin has several excellent private hospitals—Beacon Hospital, Blackrock Clinic, Mater Private. Quality is high, wait times short. Your insurance should cover these directly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I work for Irish clients on Stamp 0?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No—Stamp 0 explicitly prohibits working for Irish employers or clients. You can only do remote work for non-Irish companies/clients. This is a core condition. If you need Irish clients, consider STEP or employment-based permits.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Does Stamp 0 count toward Irish citizenship?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No—Stamp 0 is NOT reckonable residence. Time on Stamp 0 does not count toward the 5 years needed for citizenship. Stamp 0, Stamp 1A, Stamp 2, and Stamp 2A all don't count. STEP and employment permits do count.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Ireland in the Schengen Zone?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No—Ireland opted out of Schengen. An Irish residence permit does NOT give Schengen travel rights. You'll need separate visas for Schengen countries depending on your nationality. Ireland maintains its own immigration system with the UK (Common Travel Area).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How much does STEP cost?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          STEP requires €50,000 in available funding (personal funds or investment). The application fee is €350. You must have an innovative business proposal—retail, catering, and personal services are typically excluded.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How difficult is finding accommodation in Dublin?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Very difficult—Dublin has a severe housing crisis. Expect €1,800-2,800/month for a 1BR apartment, competition from 50+ viewers, and extensive documentation requirements. Consider Cork or Galway for easier (though still competitive) housing markets.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why choose Ireland over other EU countries?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Native English—no language barrier for business, daily life, or government services. Post-Brexit, Ireland is the only English-speaking EU country. Tech hub with Google, Facebook, Apple European HQs. Friendly culture. Trade-offs: high costs, not Schengen, Stamp 0 limitations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Final Verdict -->
  <section id="verdict" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Final Verdict</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Ireland offers something no other EU country can: native English. For remote workers who need an English-speaking base without language barriers, this alone can justify the high costs and Stamp 0 limitations.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The trade-offs are significant. Stamp 0 prohibits Irish clients and doesn't count toward citizenship. STEP requires €50,000 and genuine innovation. Dublin's housing crisis means brutal rental competition. And Ireland isn't in Schengen—no automatic EU travel rights.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      For the right person—remote worker serving foreign clients, comfortable with high costs, valuing English and Irish culture over Schengen access—Ireland works well. For entrepreneurs with €50,000 and innovative ideas, STEP provides a real pathway. For everyone else, Portugal or Germany may offer better overall packages.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Bottom Line</h3>
      <p class="text-primary-800 mb-4">
        Ireland's Stamp 0 works for financially self-sufficient remote workers who don't need Irish clients or citizenship pathway. STEP suits innovative entrepreneurs with €50,000. Budget €100-300/month for mandatory private health insurance—Stamp 0 holders have NO public healthcare access. The English advantage is real; evaluate whether it justifies the limitations and costs.
      </p>
